TI  - European Patterns of Corporate Ownership: A Twelve-Country Study
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 759
EP  - 778
VL  - 28
IS  - 4
AB  - A number of qualitative studies have shown striking international differences in corporate governance systems. This paper presents a quantitative analysis of ownership structures among the hundred largest companies in twelve European countries. The existence of a highly significant nation effect is confirmed. Further statistical analysis indicates that the nation effect is party explained by institutional differences.
